  "description": "Anthurium scherzerianum, commonly known as Flamingo Flower or Pigtail Anthurium, is a small epiphytic aroid native to Costa Rica. It belongs to the Araceae family and features lance-shaped to oval, dark green leaves (10-20 cm long) with prominent veins. The plant produces distinctive, colorful spathes (red, pink, orange, or white) with a curled, pigtail-like spadix, hence one of its common names. The plant displays an upright, compact growth habit and typically reaches 20-40 cm in height. In its native habitat, it grows as an epiphyte on tree trunks and branches in tropical forests. In terrariums or indoor settings, this plant adds vibrant color with its colorful spathes. It's extremely popular among aroid enthusiasts for its compact size and attractive flowers.",
